<subSubSection id="C37F6512FF90FFEDFF4C2B9BC7E02E80" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF90FFEDFF4C2B9BC7E02E80" blockId="13.[151,1437,860,1749]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis id="B911EA8BFF90FFEDFF4C2B9BC7232EDD" bold="true" box="[199,321,932,957]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal rostrum and profemora testaceous, apex of ventrite VII of females acuminated, elytral costa strongly demarcated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6512FF90FFEDFF4C2BD3C5682B08" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF90FFEDFF4C2BD3C5DF29D8" blockId="13.[151,1437,860,1749]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis id="B911EA8BFF90FFEDFF4C2BD3C7162965" bold="true" box="[199,372,1004,1029]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Redescription.</emphasis>
Head black, with rostrum dorsally testaceous, as long as antennomeres I+II (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF90FFEDFB6D2BD3C3502965" box="[1254,1330,1004,1029]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1433,1456]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,198,1400]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,193,1413]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Rostrum: 10. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 11. M. quadricostatus; 12. M. caeruleus; 13. M. germaini; 14. M. grandjeani; 15. M. subparallelus; 16. M. testaceirostris; 17. M. simoni; 18. M. kirschi. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271308/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFA9E2BD3C3502965" box="[1301,1330,1004,1029]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
); coronal suture shallow, hardly visible; median interocular distance of 
<date id="FFDB1059FF90FFEDFCFB2C2FC5EE2948" box="[880,908,1040,1064]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFCFB2C2FC51C2948" box="[880,894,1040,1064]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
the width of eyes. Mandibles short, slightly arched, testaceous, connates to labrum. Maxillary palp with palpomere I small, ca. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFBBB2C0BC258292C" box="[1072,1082,1076,1100]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFBCE2C0BC231292C" box="[1093,1107,1076,1100]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="3.0">3</number>
the length of II; palpomere II elongate, subconic; palpomeres III+IV as long as II, the last broadened, securiform. Antennae finely pubescent, scape subconic, constrict basally; pedicel small, 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFD3F2C43C4DC29F4" box="[692,702,1148,1172]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFD432C43C4BA29F4" box="[712,728,1148,1172]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="4.0">4</number>
the length of scape; antennomere III as long as the sum of I+II; III to V subequal; antennomeres V to XI gradually decreasing in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF90FFEDFF4C2CFAC5BD280D" blockId="13.[151,1437,860,1749]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Pronotum subtrapezoidal, wider than longer (
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFD7A2CFBC56329BC" box="[753,769,1220,1244]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="9.0">9</number>
: 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFC8E2CFBC54729BC" box="[773,805,1220,1244]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="12.0">12</number>
), with margins stout and rounded, angles rounded, testaceous, with a median longitudinal black stripe; a pair of longitudinal elevations parallels, broadened in middle third and less prominent in anterior and posterior region; a pair of oblique elevations in basal third region starting from 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFF5F2D0FC6822828" box="[212,224,1328,1352]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFF612D0FC69A2828" box="[234,248,1328,1352]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="4.0">4</number>
portion and reaching but not touching the broadened region in middle third of pronotum; a pair of curved longitudinal elevations parallel to median longitudinal elevations (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF90FFEDFCF52D6BC5B0280D" box="[894,978,1364,1389]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1260,1283]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,200,1229]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,193,1239]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Pronotum: 19. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 20. M. quadricostatus; 21. M. caeruleus; 22. M. germaini; 23. M. grandjeani; 24. M. simoni; 25. M. subparallelus; 26. M. testaceirostris. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271309/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFC392D6BC5B0280D" box="[946,978,1364,1389]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF90FFEDFF4C2D48C7FD289C" blockId="13.[151,1437,860,1749]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Elytra subparallel, broadened apically, with lateral margins stout, testaceous, apical third black, not reticulated. Arrangement of elytral costae: costa I and IV not fused to any other, both free; costae II and III subapically fused, this fusion continuing into a single costa (II+III); elytral costae not reaching elytral apex. Scutellum black, transverse (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF90FFEDFE932DDBC705289C" box="[280,359,1508,1533]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,204,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,195,1259]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Dorsal view: 1. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 2. M. quadricostatus; 3. M. caeruleus; 4. M. germaini; 5. M. grandjeani; 6. M. simoni; 7. Macrolygistopterus subparallelus; 8. M. testaceirostris; 9. M. kirschi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271307/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Figs. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFEDC2DDBC705289C" box="[343,359,1508,1532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="8.33">8</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF90FFEDFEF82DDBC7F0289C" box="[371,402,1508,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1714,1737]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,204,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1693]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 35. Elytra: 27. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 28. M. quadricostatus; 29. M. caeruleus; 30. M. germaini; 31. M. grandjeani; 32. M. subparallelus; 33. M. testaceirostris; 34. M. simoni; 35. M. kirschi Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271310/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF90FFEDFF4C2E38C72F2B24" blockId="13.[151,1437,860,1749]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Female ventrite VII transverse, densely pubescent, with apical region deeply notched, forming two acuminated apices (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF90FFEDFF672E13C7222B24" box="[236,320,1580,1605]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 40" captionStartId="9.[151,264,953,976]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,204,925]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[150,1436,195,932]" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 40. Female ventrite VII: 36. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 37. M. quadricostatus; 38. M. caeruleus; 39. M. grandjeani; 40. M. testaceirostris. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271311/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF90FFEDFEAB2E13C7222B24" box="[288,320,1580,1604]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF90FFEDFF4C2E70C5682B08" blockId="13.[151,1437,860,1749]" box="[199,778,1615,1640]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Width at humeri&gt; 3.4 mm. Elytral length— 
<quantity id="4C9D9B7CFF90FFEDFD3C2E70C5642B08" box="[695,774,1615,1640]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
